page.title: 06ECOLOGY - WYESHAM
page.content: {FORESTRY COMMISSION Mr. Powell, Assistant Warden from the Forest of Dean came to talk to Class 2 of Wyesham Junior School. {MAMMALS OF THE FOREST Deer, Bank Voles, Grey Squirrels,Mice, Hedgehogs, Shrews, Bats, Moles,Otters, Foxes, Badgers, Stoats, Weasels, Rabbits and Hares. {BIRDS OF THE FOREST Pied Flycatcher, Dipper, Woodcock, Jay, Long-tailed tit, Chaffinch, Tawny Owl, Great-spotted Woodpecker, Kingfisher, Coot, Swallow, Crossbill. {TREES OF THE FOREST PRINCIPAL CONIFERS - Douglas Fir, Corsican and Scots Pine, European, Japanese and Hybrid Larch, Norway Spruce, Western Red Cedar, Western Hemlock. BROADLEAVED TREES - Sessile and Pedunculate Oak, Beech and Birch.
